%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20future%20of%20homebuying%20is%20here%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20a%20whole%20lot%20better%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Gave%20coming%20down%20on%20a%20house.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6580804a50edbc52a865448e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221334%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20wave%20of%20multibillion-dollar%20lawsuits%20poses%20a%20real%20threat%20to%20the%20old%20way%20of%20buying%20and%20selling%20homes.%20In%20the%20chaos%20that%20follows%2C%20regular%20buyers%20and%20sellers%20could%20come%20out%20on%20top.%20%3Cp%3EPeter%20Dazeley%2FGetty%20Images%3B%20Jenny%20Chang-Rodriguez%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThings%20are%20not%20OK%20in%20Realtorland.%20The%20US%20housing%20market%20is%20still%20reeling%20from%20pandemic-era%20shocks%2C%20home%20sales%20are%20stuck%20in%20a%20rut%2C%20and%20mortgage%20rates%2C%20while%20inching%20downward%2C%20are%20still%20near%20two-decade%20highs.%20It's%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-ice-age-higher-home-prices-fewer-sales-inventory-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebad%20time%20to%20be%20a%20buyer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20maybe%20a%20worse%20time%20to%20be%20a%20seller.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20all%20this%20upheaval%2C%20there's%20another%20story%20brewing%20in%20which%20the%20stakes%20for%20everyone%20in%20real%20estate%2C%20from%20agents%20to%20the%20average%20consumer%2C%20are%20even%20higher.%20It%20won't%20have%20anything%20to%20do%20with%20the%20debate%20over%20whether%20you%20should%20put%20your%20hard-earned%20cash%20toward%20rent%20or%20a%20down%20payment.%20Instead%2C%20it'll%20be%20about%20court%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20threat%20facing%20the%20industry%20is%20a%20mounting%20wave%20of%20class-action%20lawsuits%20that%20accuse%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Realtors%2C%20along%20with%20some%20of%20the%20country's%20biggest%20real-estate%20brokerages%2C%20of%20conspiring%20to%20rip%20off%20consumers%20by%20keeping%20the%20commissions%20paid%20to%20agents%20unfairly%20high.%20These%20cases%20are%20expected%20to%20reach%20major%20milestones%20in%20the%20next%20year%2C%20and%20the%20ramifications%20could%20be%20staggering%3A%20Tens%2C%20if%20not%20hundreds%2C%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars%20hang%20in%20the%20balance.%20Hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-agents-realtors-reckoning-housing-market-home-sales-slow-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERealtors%20could%20see%20their%20commissions%20slashed%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20might%20force%20many%20out%20of%20the%20business.%20The%20old%20way%20of%20buying%20and%20selling%20homes%20could%20go%20away%20forever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E2024%20will%20mark%20the%20beginning%20of%20a%20great%20experiment%20in%20real%20estate.%20The%20status%20quo%20won't%20change%20overnight%20%E2%80%94%20there%20will%20be%20more%20courtroom%20showdowns%20before%20that%20happens%20%E2%80%94%20but%20some%20forward-thinking%20brokerages%20and%20agents%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20handful%20of%20startups%2C%20are%20already%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20comes%20next.%20Things%20are%20about%20to%20get%20really%20weird%20%E2%80%94%20and%20for%20American%20homebuyers%2C%20that%20could%20be%20great%20news.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20old%20way%20in%20jeopardy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you've%20bought%20a%20home%2C%20you%20probably%20never%20cut%20a%20check%20to%20the%20agent%20who%20held%20your%20hand%20through%20the%20ordeal.%20For%20decades%2C%20agent%20commissions%20have%20been%20mostly%20out%20of%20sight%20and%20out%20of%20mind%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Efor%20homebuyers.%20But%20in%202024%2C%20many%20buyers%20and%20sellers%20may%20have%20to%20start%20thinking%20hard%20about%20just%20how%20much%20they're%20willing%20to%20pay%20their%20real-estate%20agents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20house%20trades%20hands%2C%20the%20money%20usually%20works%20its%20way%20down%20a%20circuitous%20path%20%E2%80%94%20the%20buyer%20pays%20the%20seller%2C%20who%20uses%20a%20slice%20of%20that%20sum%20(usually%205%25%20to%206%25%20of%20the%20final%20sale%20price)%20to%20pay%20their%20agent%2C%20who%20then%20splits%20that%20money%20with%20the%20buyer's%20agent.%20I've%20previously%20written%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-agents-lawsuits-buy-sell-homes-forever-housing-market-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhy%20the%20system%20works%20this%20way%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flawsuits-verdict-realtors-brokerages-real-estate-agents-home-buying-selling-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earguments%20for%20and%20against%20the%20model%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20as%20a%20recap%3A%20Consumer%20advocates%20say%20this%20setup%20discourages%20market%20competition%20between%20agents.%20If%20you're%20a%20buyer%2C%20you%20want%20to%20pay%20as%20little%20as%20possible%2C%20but%20your%20agent%20stands%20to%20make%20more%20if%20the%20home%20price%20goes%20up.%20Plus%2C%20it's%20the%20seller%20who%20decides%20what%20percentage%20each%20agent%20will%20make%20before%20even%20listing%20their%20house.%20As%20John%20Kwoka%2C%20an%20economist%20and%20antitrust%20researcher%20at%20Northeastern%20University%2C%20told%20me%3A%20The%20incentives%20aren't%20aligned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20NAR%20argues%20the%20system%20is%20designed%20to%20get%20a%20deal%20closed%20as%20efficiently%20as%20possible.%20When%20an%20offer%20comes%20in%2C%20there's%20no%20bickering%20over%20commissions%20%E2%80%94%20everyone%20already%20knows%20who%20will%20get%20paid%20what.%20And%20the%20NAR%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20brokerages%20named%20in%20the%20lawsuits%2C%20has%20maintained%20that%20commissions%20are%20always%20negotiable.%20If%20you're%20a%20seller%20and%20you%20want%20the%20agents%20to%20split%20only%201%25%20of%20the%20sale%20price%20%E2%80%94%20or%20even%200%25%20%E2%80%94%20you%20can%20do%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20major%20lawsuit%20to%20put%20this%20argument%20to%20the%20test%2C%20Sitzer%2FBurnett%20v.%20NAR%2C%20went%20to%20trial%20in%202023%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20wasn't%20pretty%20for%20the%20real-estate%20establishment.%20On%20Halloween%2C%20jurors%20deliberated%20for%20just%20a%20few%20hours%20before%20finding%20the%20defendants%20liable%2C%20siding%20with%20thousands%20of%20home%20sellers%20who%20claimed%20they'd%20been%20strong-armed%20into%20paying%20their%20agents%20the%20customary%205%25%20to%206%25%20of%20the%20sale%20price%20and%20dishing%20out%20%245.3%20billion%20in%20damages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20if%20the%20case%20has%20cracked%20open%20the%20door%20to%20major%20changes%20to%20the%20commission%20model%2C%202024%20is%20shaping%20up%20to%20be%20the%20year%20it'll%20be%20knocked%20down.%20The%20first%20thing%20to%20watch%20for%20will%20be%20an%20official%20ruling%20from%20the%20judge%20in%20the%20Sitzer%2FBurnett%20case%2C%20expected%20sometime%20in%20the%20spring.%20While%20the%20jury%20has%20already%20sided%20with%20the%20plaintiffs%2C%20the%20judge%20still%20needs%20to%20decide%20which%20kinds%20of%20actions%20the%20NAR%20and%20the%20brokerages%20will%20need%20to%20take%20to%20remedy%20the%20situation.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20it's%20pretty%20clear%20what%20the%20plaintiffs%20and%20their%20lawyers%20want%3A%20They%20argue%20for%20%26quot%3Bdecoupling%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20changing%20the%20rules%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20buyers%20and%20sellers%20pay%20their%20agents%20separately.%20At%20the%20most%20extreme%20end%2C%20buyer's%20and%20seller's%20agents%20might%20be%20expressly%20prohibited%20from%20splitting%20commissions.%20The%20NAR%20has%20vowed%20to%20appeal%20the%20verdict%2C%20and%20said%20it%20expects%20arguments%20to%20take%20place%20later%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20a%20ruling%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20decoupling%2C%20a%20larger%20case%2C%20Moehrl%20v.%20NAR%2C%20should%20reach%20trial%20in%20the%20last%20quarter%20of%202024.%20That%20suit%20involves%20sellers%20from%20a%20broad%20swath%20of%20the%20US%2C%20including%20Dallas%2C%20Phoenix%2C%20Philadelphia%2C%20and%20Miami%2C%20and%20damages%20could%20stack%20up%20to%20more%20than%20%2440%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20class-action%20attorneys%20are%20bringing%20lawsuits%20as%20well.%20The%20two%20big%20cases%20so%20far%20have%20focused%20on%20home%20sellers%2C%20but%20a%20new%20case%20filed%20in%20November%2C%20known%20as%20Batton%202%2C%20takes%20aim%20at%20brokerages%20such%20as%20Douglas%20Elliman%2C%20Compass%2C%20and%20Redfin%20on%20behalf%20of%20a%20nationwide%20group%20of%20%3Cem%3Ebuyers%3C%2Fem%3E.%20It's%20not%20yet%20clear%20how%20big%20the%20damages%20could%20be%20in%20this%20case%2C%20but%20the%20sheer%20size%20of%20the%20plaintiff%20class%20points%20to%20a%20much-larger%20figure%20than%20that%20of%20the%20Moehrl%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20head%20plaintiff%20in%20the%20Sitzer%20case%20has%20filed%20another%20nationwide%20class-action%20suit%20against%20the%20NAR%20and%20brokerages%20that%20weren't%20included%20in%20the%20original%20case%2C%20including%20Compass%2C%20eXp%2C%20and%20Redfin.%20While%20these%20cases%20won't%20reach%20trial%20anytime%20soon%2C%20they%20put%20increasing%20pressure%20on%20the%20industry%20to%20find%20ways%20to%20settle%2C%20rather%20than%20risk%20years%20of%20time-consuming%20and%20costly%20litigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20new%20age%20of%20experimentation%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20real-estate%20agents%20may%20wait%20until%20a%20ruling%20from%20the%20judge%20in%20the%20Sitzer%2FBurnett%20case%20before%20changing%20their%20practices%2C%20or%20hold%20out%20hope%20until%20the%20last%20appeal%20has%20worked%20its%20way%20through%20the%20courts.%20Others%20have%20read%20the%20writing%20on%20the%20wall%20and%20are%20already%20starting%20to%20get%20creative%20with%20how%20they%20get%20paid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20matter%20of%20allowing%20alternatives%20to%20be%20experimented%20with%20and%20see%20what%20sticks%2C%26quot%3B%20Kwoka%2C%20the%20Northeastern%20economist%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20about%20to%20do%20that%2C%20ready%20or%20not.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20those%20who%20think%20the%20jury%20got%20it%20wrong%20are%20accepting%20that%20commissions%20are%20likely%20going%20to%20change.%20That%20group%20includes%20Brian%20Boero%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%201000watt%2C%20a%20brand%20and%20strategy%20agency%20that%20advises%20real-estate%20brokerages%20and%20mortgage%20companies.%20Boero%20said%20he's%20busy%20prepping%20his%20clients%20for%20the%20reality%20of%20decoupling%2C%20a%20scenario%20that%20he%20expects%20to%20arrive%20%26quot%3Bsooner%20rather%20than%20later.%26quot%3B%20According%20to%20Boero%2C%20the%20key%20for%20agents%20is%20to%20clearly%20explain%20to%20buyers%20what%20they%20do%2C%20how%20they%20get%20paid%2C%20and%20why%20they%20may%20need%20to%20start%20getting%20paid%20differently.%20In%20many%20instances%2C%20those%20conversations%20have%20been%20conveniently%20swept%20under%20the%20rug%20for%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20going%20to%20be%20real-estate%20agents%20who%20are%20not%20able%20to%20articulate%2C%20let%20alone%20demonstrate%2C%20their%20value%2C%26quot%3B%20Boero%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BThose%20folks%20will%20probably%20be%20out%20of%20the%20business%20very%20quickly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20buyer's%20agents%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%20the%20competent%20ones%20%E2%80%94%20will%20be%20fine.%20After%20all%2C%20despite%20all%20kinds%20of%20technological%20advances%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbuying-a-home-house-too-complicated-amazon-real-estate-market-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20people%20are%20using%20agents%20today%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20they%20were%20before%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20would%20be%20foolish%20to%20buy%20a%20home%20without%20an%20expert%20helping%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20Boero%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20also%20think%20that%20a%20smaller%2C%20smarter%2C%20more%20professional%20real-estate%20industry%20is%20going%20to%20come%20out%20of%20this%2C%20and%20I%20think%20that's%20a%20good%20thing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22house%20for%20sale%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f09cc8ed66760019da81e5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222001%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BIn%20this%20new%20world%20order%2C%20the%20agent%20and%20the%20client%20will%20have%20the%20flexibility%20to%20negotiate%20something%20that%20makes%20sense%20for%20them%20both.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EThe%20Good%20Brigade%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDecoupling%20also%20opens%20the%20door%20to%20further%20experimentation%20with%20agents'%20fees.%20Joe%20Stockton%2C%20an%20attorney%20who%20previously%20worked%20at%20Zillow%20and%20has%20spent%20years%20thinking%20about%20creative%20fee%20arrangements%2C%20described%20to%20me%20one%20possibility%3A%20a%20tiered%20system%20in%20which%20buyers%20pay%20more%20for%20progressively%20broader%20offerings.%20At%20the%20top%20would%20be%20the%20%26quot%3Bwhite-glove%20service%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20what%20you%20might%20expect%20of%20a%20sought-after%20agent%20today%20%E2%80%94%20the%20market%20insights%2C%20the%20pavement%20pounding%20in%20search%20of%20the%20best%20deals%2C%20all%20those%20hours%20spent%20advising%20and%20consoling%20and%20haggling%20with%20the%20sellers.%20Something%20like%20this%20could%20command%20%24250%20an%20hour%2C%20like%20a%20good%20lawyer%2C%20but%20be%20capped%20at%20some%20percentage%20of%20the%20sale%20price%2C%20like%203.5%25.%20The%20tier%20below%20would%20offer%20good%20service%20but%20wouldn't%20go%20above%20and%20beyond%2C%20and%20would%20notably%20exclude%20all%20that%20initial%20legwork%3B%20the%20agent%20could%20step%20in%20once%20you'd%20already%20found%20your%20options%20online%20and%20would%20command%20a%20smaller%20fee%2C%20like%201.5%25%20of%20the%20sale%20price.%20At%20the%20most%20basic%20level%2C%20an%20agent%20could%20charge%20%242%2C000%20for%20just%20making%20sure%20that%20nothing%20goes%20awry%20%E2%80%94%20you'd%20get%20none%20of%20the%20hand-holding%20and%20advisory%20services%2C%20but%20you%20wouldn't%20have%20to%20pay%20for%20them%2C%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20either%20situation%2C%20a%20one-size-fits-all%20compensation%20model%20and%20fee%20structure%20doesn't%20make%20sense%2C%26quot%3B%20Stockton%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BIn%20this%20new%20world%20order%2C%20the%20agent%20and%20the%20client%20will%20have%20the%20flexibility%20to%20negotiate%20something%20that%20makes%20sense%20for%20them%20both.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20agents%20are%20mostly%20incentivized%20to%20close%20a%20transaction%20quickly%20%E2%80%94%20a%20%2410%2C000%20difference%20in%20the%20sale%20price%20would%20shift%20the%20amount%20an%20agent%20gets%20paid%20by%20only%20about%20%24300%20on%20the%20high%20end.%20But%20there's%20a%20world%20in%20which%20a%20buyer's%20agent's%20cut%20goes%20%3Cem%3Eup%3C%2Fem%3E%20if%20they're%20able%20to%20knock%20%2450%2C000%20off%20the%20list%20price%2C%20or%20if%20they%20find%20you%20a%20deal%20below%20a%20certain%20dollar%20amount%20that%20meets%20your%20criteria.%20Similar%20incentives%20could%20be%20baked%20into%20the%20commission%20for%20a%20seller's%20agent%20as%20well.%20Nic%20Johnson%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20ListWise%2C%20is%20working%20on%20such%20a%20solution%3A%20The%20company%20proposes%20a%20model%20in%20which%20agents%20bid%20for%20listings%2C%20which%20effectively%20sets%20the%20terms%20for%20how%20much%20they%20want%20to%20make%20if%20they're%20able%20to%20boost%20the%20price%20of%20your%20home.%20So%20while%20an%20agent%20might%20be%20guaranteed%20only%20a%200.75%25%20commission%20if%20the%20home%20sells%20for%20a%20predetermined%20baseline%20price%2C%20they%20may%20stand%20to%20increase%20that%20cut%20by%20several%20percentage%20points%20if%20the%20price%20goes%20up%20by%20%2450%2C000%20or%20%24100%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20need%20to%20make%20it%20so%20that%20the%20agent's%20pay%20meaningfully%20varies%20based%20on%20different%20sale%20prices%2C%26quot%3B%20Johnson%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BTo%20me%2C%20that's%20really%20the%20important%20thing%3A%20making%20sure%20the%20agent's%20incentives%20are%20aligned%20with%20the%20homeowner's.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20all%20sounds%20pretty%20good%20for%20regular%20buyers%20and%20sellers%20%E2%80%94%20lower%20fees%2C%20a%20clearer%20picture%20of%20what%20you're%20paying%20for%2C%20and%20a%20greater%20emphasis%20on%20negotiating%20rather%20than%20accepting%20the%20status%20quo.%20An%20analysis%20from%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Consumer%20Federation%20of%20America%20estimated%20that%20American%20consumers%20could%20save%20as%20much%20as%20%2420%20billion%20to%20%2430%20billion%20every%20year%20if%20commission%20rates%20fell%20in%20line%20with%20those%20of%20other%20developed%20markets%2C%20such%20as%20Australia%2C%20the%20Netherlands%2C%20and%20the%20UK.%20But%20there%20may%20be%20downsides%2C%20particularly%20for%20buyers%20who%20might%20not%20have%20enough%20cash%20on%20hand%20to%20pay%20their%20agents%20out%20of%20pocket.%20There%20are%20possible%20solutions%20%E2%80%94%20industry%20bigwigs%20could%20push%20for%20changes%20to%20mortgage%20rules%20so%20that%20commissions%20would%20be%20folded%20into%20a%20loan%2C%20or%20sellers%20could%20agree%20to%20give%20buyers%20rebates%20so%20they%20can%20pay%20their%20agents%20after%20a%20sale%20closes%20%E2%80%94%20but%20they're%20far%20from%20guaranteed%20at%20this%20point.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20those%20kinds%20of%20fixes