0had%20a%20bubbly%2C%20outgoing%20personality%20and%20a%20sales%20background%2C%20while%20they%20were%20primarily%20introverted%20intellects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Col%20start%3D%5C%223%5C%22%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20undiagnosed%20ADHD%20meant%20struggling%20to%20make%20early%20morning%20meetings%20or%20read%20long%20documents%20%E2%80%94%20things%20that%20seemed%20so%20simple%20for%20everyone%20else%20and%20impossible%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20this%20triggered%20feelings%20of%20imposter%20syndrome%20and%20doubt%20in%20myself.%20I%20questioned%20whether%20someone%20like%20me%20was%20really%20cut%20out%20to%20be%20at%20the%20executive%20table.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20there%20was%20a%20group%20of%20executives%2C%20including%20the%20CEO%2C%20who%20would%20go%20for%20lunch%20on%20Thursdays%20to%20talk%20strategy.%20If%20you%20got%20invited%2C%20you%20were%20in%20the%20club.%20In%20my%20five%20years%20as%20a%20director%2C%20I%20never%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20next%20five%20years%2C%20I%20worked%20my%20tail%20off%2C%20hoping%20to%20land%20a%20promotion%20to%20VP.%20I%20poured%20my%20heart%20and%20soul%20into%20trying%20to%20get%20the%20business%20off%20the%20ground.%20I%20put%20in%20long%20days%20and%20worked%20in%20the%20evenings.%20This%20meant%20answering%20emails%20the%20minute%20I%20opened%20my%20eyes%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20rarely%20taking%20a%20real%20lunch%20break%20and%20being%20'on'%2024-7.%20I%20never%20took%20a%20vacation%20without%20my%20phone%20and%20made%20myself%20the%20'go-to'%20for%20anything%20my%20team%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20biggest%20sacrifice%20was%20the%20travel.%20I%20recall%20one%20trip%20to%20California%20in%20particular.%20I%20was%20traveling%20with%20one%20of%20my%20reps%20to%20try%20and%20close%20business.%20The%20pressure%20was%20on%20because%20we%20weren't%20hitting%20our%20numbers%2C%20and%20I%20felt%20this%20reflected%20my%20own%20ability%20to%20be%20an%20executive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20a%20note%20from%20my%20son's%20school%20saying%20their%20kindergarten%20graduation%20would%20be%20on%20the%20Thursday%20that%20I%20was%20gone.%20My%20heart%20sank.%20I%20couldn't%20cancel%20the%20work%20trip%20so%2C%20as%20I%20always%20did%2C%20I%20put%20my%20job%20first.%20I%20tried%20to%20video%20call%20from%20the%20car%2C%20but%20we%20lost%20connection.%20I%20missed%20the%20whole%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20realize%20how%20much%20the%20stress%20of%20my%20job%20was%20impacting%20my%20relationships%20and%20my%20physical%20and%20mental%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20was%20even%20told%20I%20may%20need%20to%20accept%20that%20I%20might%20never%20be%20a%20VP%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20brought%20up%20my%20VP%20promotion%20to%20my%20boss%20every%20chance%20I%20got%20%E2%80%94%20during%20annual%20reviews%20as%20well%20as%20in%20our%201-on-1%20meetings.%20I%20must%20have%20had%20at%20least%20two%20dozen%20conversations%20with%20him%20about%20this%2C%20with%20me%20trying%20to%20convince%20him%20to%20give%20me%20the%20title%2C%20and%20each%20time%2C%20he%20responded%20that%20I%20needed%20to%20be%20more%20strategic%2C%20and%20I%20just%20wasn't%20there%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20to%20wonder%20whether%20I%20should%20consider%20a%20different%20career%20path.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20after%20eight%20and%20a%20half%20years%20with%20the%20company%2C%20I%20decided%20it%20was%20time%20to%20make%20a%20change.%20I%20was%20having%20lunch%20with%20a%20VP%20I%20had%20worked%20for%20previously%20and%20mentioned%20I%20was%20considering%20my%20options.%20To%20my%20utter%20surprise%2C%20he%20suggested%20a%20VP%20sales%20opportunity%20he%20thought%20I%20was%20perfect%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELong%20story%20short%2C%20I%20got%20the%20role.%20I%20was%20actually%20going%20to%20be%20a%20VP%20%E2%80%94%20I%20finally%20made%20it%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20dream%20came%20true.%20But%20it%20wasn't%20what%20I%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EC-suite%20execs%20and%20VPs%20were%20treating%20me%20like%20I%20had%20all%20of%20the%20knowledge.%20They%20were%20asking%20my%20advice%20on%20things%20%E2%80%94%20and%20listening.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%20this%20surprised%20me%2C%20and%20worried%20me%20a%20little.%20Would%20I%20be%20able%20to%20live%20up%20to%20their%20expectations%3F%20Clearly%2C%20they%20thought%20I%20was%20a%20whole%20lot%20smarter%20than%20I%20actually%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20realized%20that%20I%20was%20just%20as%20capable%20as%20them%20and%20had%20been%20so%20all%20along.%20I%20was%20the%20same%20person%20I%20was%20before%20the%20VP%20title%2C%20with%20the%20exact%20same%20knowledge%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20not%20like%20after%20I%20became%20VP%20I%20suddenly%20became%20200%25%20wiser.%20But%20because%20I%20was%20now%20a%20VP%2C%20people%20were%20listening%20to%20me%2C%20and%20it%20was%20hard%20for%20me%20to%20reconcile%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20years%20of%20not%20being%20part%20of%20the%20club%2C%20I%20had%20created%20a%20narrative%20in%20my%20head%20that%20the%20people%20at%20the%20table%20had%20something%20that%20I%20didn't%20have%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I%20may%20never%20have.%20But%20the%20truth%20was%20they%20weren't%20any%20smarter%2C%20more%20talented%2C%20or%20special.%20It%20struck%20me%20that%20my%20colleagues%20were%20actually%20just%20like%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20years%20into%20my%20role%2C%20I%20was%20contacted%20by%20a%20recruiter%20for%20an%20EVP%20role.%20This%20was%20a%20real%20seat%20at%20the%20table.%20I%20took%20the%20call%20thinking%20there%20was%20no%20way%20I'd%20actually%20get%20an%20offer.%20But%20sure%20enough%2C%20after%20a%20couple%20of%20rounds%20of%20interviews%2C%20I%20got%20the%20job%20and%20accepted%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStarting%20my%20EVP%20role%20was%20nerve-wracking.%20But%20I%20got%20to%20learn%20my%20lesson%20all%20over%20again.%20Here%20I%20was%2C%20part%20of%20a%20talented%20team%20of%20high-achieving%20execs.%20