%20the%20outdoors%2C%20trails%2C%20and%20exploring%2C%20and%20I%20knew%20I%20wanted%20to%20do%20more%20of%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20knew%20I%20didn't%20necessarily%20want%20to%20stay%20in%20California%3B%20instead%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20expand%20my%20horizons%20and%20see%20something%20new.%20So%2C%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20when%20I%20had%20to%20return%20home%20from%20college%20in%20Minnesota%2C%20I%20decided%20on%20Colorado.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20partner%20is%20from%20Colorado%2C%20which%20made%20the%20transition%20easier.%20After%20lining%20up%20a%20job%20in%20the%20sustainability%20field%2C%20I%20packed%20up%20my%20stuff%20and%20made%20the%20move%20to%20Lakewood%2C%20a%20Denver%20suburb.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20got%20here%2C%20I%20began%20exploring%20different%20mountain%20towns%2C%20and%20I%20learned%20how%20to%20hike%20in%20snowy%20conditions%20%E2%80%94%20something%20I%20didn't%20learn%20in%20California.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20that%20I%20live%20in%20Colorado%2C%20I%20love%20it%20for%20many%20reasons.%20Everything%20here%20is%20super%20pretty%2C%20and%20there's%20always%20something%20to%20do%2C%20like%20winter%20hikes%20through%20the%20snow.%20I%20have%20an%20endless%20list%20of%20places%20to%20explore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20are%20three%20things%20about%20moving%20to%20Denver%2C%20Colorado%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethat%20were%20surprising%20to%20me%20personally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20The%20lack%20of%20diversity%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20grew%20up%20in%20the%20bay%20area%20of%20California%2C%20which%20is%20very%20diverse.%20There%20are%20people%20from%20all%20ethnicities%20and%20backgrounds%2C%20and%20this%20diversity%20is%20also%20reflected%20in%20the%20food%20options.%20I%20was%20used%20to%20going%20to%20really%20good%20Asian%20restaurants%20and%20picking%20up%20a%20bag%20handmade%20dumplings%20to%20cook%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Denver%20feels%20predominantly%20white.%20There%20are%20also%20a%20lot%20of%20breweries%20here%2C%20and%20I'm%20not%20saying%20it's%20a%20bad%20thing%2C%20but%20it%20does%20feel%20different%20from%20what%20I'm%20used%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20The%20busy%20I-70%20traffic%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20also%20used%20to%20traffic%20in%20California%2C%20but%20the%20traffic%20in%20Denver%20surprised%20me.%20More%20specifically%2C%20it's%20the%20I-70%20that%20becomes%20packed%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it's%20crazy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20ton%20of%20people%20who%20do%20day%20trips%20and%20head%20to%20the%20mountains.%20I%20learned%20that%20if%20you're%20heading%20to%20the%20mountains%20for%20a%20day%20of%20skiing%2C%20you%20will%20want%20to%20leave%20at%206%20a.m.%2C%20if%20not%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20don't%20leave%20early%20enough%2C%20you%20might%20be%20stuck%20in%20at%20least%20two%20hours%20worth%20of%20traffic.%20Then%2C%20on%20the%20drive%20back%20home%2C%20there's%20even%20more%20traffic%20to%20sit%20through.%20To%20me%2C%20it%20just%20felt%20so%20surprising%20how%20many%20people%20were%20actually%20out%20on%20the%20road%20that%20early.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20The%20quick%20changes%20in%20the%20weather%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20heard%20people%20talk%20about%20how%20quickly%20the%20weather%20changes%20and%20how%20you%20could%20experience%20all%20four%20seasons%20in%20one%20day.%20I%20thought%20it%20was%20an%20exaggeration%20until%20I%20experienced%20it%20for%20myself.%20The%20sky%20might%20be%20a%20beautiful%20blue%2C%20and%20within%2010%20minutes%20it's%20thunder%20storming.%20Then%2C%20in%20another%2010%20minutes%2C%20it's%20sunny%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20a%20time%20where%20I%20was%20hiking%20and%20the%20weather%20was%20warm%20enough%20to%20wear%20a%20tank%20top%20and%20shorts%2C%20then%20halfway%20through%20my%20hike%20it%20started%20raining%20and%20hailing.%20By%20the%20time%20I%20finished%20my%20hike%20it%20was%20warm%20again.%20This%20is%20very%20different%20from%20my%20experience%20in%20California.%20Now%2C%20I%20know%20to%2