lunteers%20%E2%80%93%20friends%20and%20social%20media%20connections%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0who%20helped%20me%20construct%20the%20house.%20I%20got%20some%20materials%20for%20free%2C%20such%20as%20pallets%20and%20old%20fencing%2C%20which%20I%20used%20for%20siding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20house%20was%20just%2010%20feet%20by%2010%20feet%2C%20which%20was%20relatively%20comfortable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20hardest%20thing%20about%20living%20off%20the%20grid%20is%20being%20responsible%20for%20everything%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDepending%20on%20what%20off-grid%20set-up%20I'm%20living%20in%2C%20I%20am%20responsible%20for%20collecting%20water%20and%20disposing%20of%20waste.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20living%20on%20the%20grid%20often%20don't%20think%20about%20water%20usage.%20Off%20the%20grid%2C%20you%20have%20to%20pay%20attention%20unless%20you%20have%20a%20well%20or%20running%20river.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Robin%20Greenfield%20storing%20and%20preparing%20his%20food.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6581a638cefc010bea24da4f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhen%20Greenfield%20is%20living%20completely%20off%20the%20grid%20he%20has%20to%20prepare%20and%20store%20all%20the%20food%20he%20collects.%3Cp%3ESarah%20Tew%20Photography%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20summer%20of%202021%20and%20again%20in%20the%20summer%20of%202023%2C%20I%20lived%20in%20a%20tiny%20house%20at%20the%20Wild%20Abundance%2C%20a%20school%20for%20carpentry%2C%20earth%20skills%2C%20and%20permaculture%20located%20near%20Asheville%2C%20NC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20off-grid%20structure%2C%20my%20water%20source%20was%20rain%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0how%20much%20you%20have%20is%20limited%20by%20how%20much%20you%20can%20store.%20If%20rain%20wasn't%20enough%2C%20I%20would%20have%20to%20walk%20to%20a%20spring%20five%20minutes%20away%20to%20fill%20jugs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20have%20no%20government%20ID%20and%20earn%20under%20the%20poverty%20threshold%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20expenses%20vary%20greatly.%20Most%20of%20my%20money%20goes%20to%20food.%20If%20I%20am%20traveling%2C%20I%20spend%20more%20on%20food.%20If%20I'm%20in%20one%20place%2C%20I%20spend%20less%20as%20I%20prefer%20to%20grow%20and%20forage%20most%20of%20what%20I%20eat.%20I%20spend%20a%20lot%20on%20seeds%2C%20plants%2C%20supplies%2C%20or%20tools%20to%20store%20food%20like%20a%20dehydrator%20or%20pressure%20canner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%2090%25%20of%20my%20possessions%20now%20are%20for%20food%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0the%20food%20itself%2C%20storage%2C%20and%20cooking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20I%20own%20600%20items%20and%20300%20of%20them%20are%20jars%20for%20food.%20I%20currently%20don't%20have%20a%20refrigerator%20or%20freezer%20so%20all%20my%20food%20has%20to%20be%20stored%20at%20ambient%20temperatures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Foraged%20and%20fermented%20foods.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6581a874cefc010bea24db43%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGreenfield%20forages%20and%20ferments%20or%20jars%20most%20of%20his%20food.%3Cp%3ERobin%20Greenfield%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20food%2C%20I%20spend%20the%20most%20on%20getting%20around%3A%20trains%2C%20buses%2C%20or%20paying%20for%20gas%20when%20I%20catch%20rides%20with%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20important%20for%20me%20to%20completely%20remove%20myself%20from%20capitalist%20systems%20I%20don't%20support.%20I%20have%20committed%20to%20not%20paying%20federal%20taxes%20therefore%20I%20earn%20less%20than%20the%20poverty%20threshold%2C%20which%20is%20%2411%2C000%20a%20year.%20Any%20income%20I%20make%20over%20this%20from%20press%20or%20books%20I've%20written%2C%20I%20donate.%20I%20have%20no%20form%20of%20ID.%20I%20don't%20drive%2C%20so%20I%20don't%20need%20a%20license.%20Last%20year%2C%20I%20destroyed%20my%20passport.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20way%20I%20live%20is%20an%20experiment%20in%20existence.%20We%20believe%20the%20norm%20is%20the%20only%20way%20but%20there%20are%20many%20other%20ways%20to%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20longer%20I%20live%20in%20this%20way%2C%20the%20less%20I%20need%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Robin%20Greenfield%20harvesting%20wild%20rice%20in%20North%20Carolina.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6581aad3cefc010bea24dc87%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERobin%20Greenfield%20harvesting%20wild%20rice.%3Cp%3ERobet%20Greenfield%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20people%20tell%20me%20that%20they're%20thinking%20of%20living%20tiny%2C%20I%20tell%20them%20to%20start%20by%20downsizing%20their%20lives.%20Get%20rid%20of%20things%20you%20don't%20need%20that%20don't%20serve%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20you%20commit%20to%20living%20in%20any%20kind%20of%20tiny%20house%2C%20travel%20and%20stay%20in%20a%20few.%20Get%20a%20feel%20for%20what%20you%20like.%20If%20you%20have%20minimal%20money%2C%20building%20yourself%20is%20key.%20Schools%20like%20Wild%20Abundance%20can%20teach%20you%20how%20to%20build%20a%20tiny%20house%20from%20the%20ground%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20am%20in%20love%20with%20the%20earth.%20The%20more%20time%20I%20spend%20outside%20and%20living%20in%20gratitude%2C%20the%20more%20I%20find%20that%20I%20don't%20need%20things.%20This%20lifestyle%20is%20not%20about%20giving%20things%20up.%20It's%20about%20filling%20your%20heart%20with%20something%20more%20meaningful%20than%20materialism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flive-off-the-grid-tiny-house-no-electricity-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1